Class AbstractUser_mxJPO

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
Group_mxJPO, PersonAdmin_mxJPO, Role_mxJPO
public abstract class AbstractUser_mxJPO
extends AbstractAdminObject_mxJPO

The class is used to export, create, delete and update common user information within MX. Common user information are all workspace related objects.

parse

protected void parse(String _url,
                     String _content)

Parses all common user specific URL values. This includes:

  • site
  • cues
  • filters
  • queries
  • tables
  • tips
  • tool sets
  • views

If an _url is included in IGNORED_URLS, this URL is ignored.

parse in class AbstractAdminObject_mxJPO
Parameters:
_url - URL to parse
_content - content of the URL to parse

writeEnd

protected void writeEnd(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                        Appendable _out)
                 throws IOException

Writes specific information about the cached role to the given writer instance. The included information is:

  • cues
  • filters
  • queries
  • tables
  • tips
  • tool sets
  • views

The workspace specific objects are only written to the TCL update file if the name of this user object does not match to the matches defined with the parameter PARAM_IGNORE_WSO_USERS.

Overrides:
writeEnd in class AbstractAdminObject_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_out - appendable instance to the TCL update file
Throws:
IOException - if the TCL update code could not written
See Also:
ignoreWorkspaceObjects(ParameterCache_mxJPO)

update

protected void update(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                      CharSequence _preMQLCode,
                      CharSequence _postMQLCode,
                      CharSequence _preTCLCode,
                      Map<String,String> _tclVariables,
                      File _sourceFile)
               throws Exception

The method overwrites the original method to append the MQL statements in the _preMQLCode to reset this user. Following steps are done:

  • remove assigned site
  • remove all cues
  • remove all filters
  • remove all queries
  • remove all tables
  • remove all tips
  • remove all tool sets
  • remove all views

The workspace specific objects are only removed if the name of this user object does not match to the matches defined with the parameter PARAM_IGNORE_WSO_USERS.

Overrides:
update in class AbstractAdminObject_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_preMQLCode - MQL statements which must be called before the TCL code is executed
_postMQLCode - MQL statements which must be called after the TCL code is executed
_preTCLCode - TCL code which is defined before the source file is sourced
_tclVariables - map of all TCL variables where the key is the name and the value is value of the TCL variable (the value is automatically converted to TCL syntax!)
_sourceFile - souce file with the TCL code to update
Throws:
Exception - if the update from derived class failed
See Also:
ignoreWorkspaceObjects(ParameterCache_mxJPO)

ignoreWorkspaceObjects

protected boolean ignoreWorkspaceObjects(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache)
Calculates if workspace objects for this user are not handled. This is done by checking if the name of this user matches one of the match lists defined with parameter PARAM_IGNORE_WSO_USERS. In this case the the workspace objects are ignored for this user.

Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
Returns:
true if the handling of workspace objects for this user is ignored
See Also:
PARAM_IGNORE_WSO_USERS
